      "A trailer should build — shots shorten and cuts quicken toward the climax; the change in rhythm is what pulls people along.",
      "Use tension and release, cut on the beat, and give the button its own air so it lands.",
      "Judge pacing by feel — watch it back repeatedly, trust where you sense a sag or rush, and fix those moments.",
      "Keep it short — most full trailers run 1:30–2:30, and almost every trailer improves when you cut more out.",
